      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "Human Appeal's operational strength lies in its ability to deliver direct services in high-risk environments. Their <cite id=\"13\">cost per beneficiary is approximately $100.85</cite>, which is considered excellent for the extreme poverty sector. This efficiency is paired with a long institutional history of <cite id=\"14\">over 30 years of service</cite>. Furthermore, the organization has achieved <cite id=\"15\">perfect 100/100 scores in Culture and Leadership</cite> from Charity Navigator, suggesting a stable and well-governed internal environment despite the complexities of international aid."
      ],
      "summary": "Human Appeal Inc is a global humanitarian organization that has been operating since <cite id=\"1\">its founding in 1991</cite>, dedicated to alleviating poverty and social injustice. The organization reported <cite id=\"2\">total revenue of $10,889,699</cite> in 2023, reflecting a massive <cite id=\"3\">3-year revenue CAGR of 268.1%</cite>. Human Appeal specializes in emergency relief and long-term development across <cite id=\"4\">high-conflict regions including Gaza, Yemen, and Syria</cite>. Their impact is significant; for instance, they provided <cite id=\"5\">over 45 million hot meals in Gaza</cite> and facilitated <cite id=\"6\">clean water for nearly 60 million people</cite> in the same region. Beyond emergency response, the charity maintains a robust <cite id=\"7\">one-to-one orphan sponsorship program</cite> that provides essential shelter, food, and education. As a <cite id=\"8\">zakat-eligible organization</cite>, it serves all eight asnaf categories, including the poor (fuqara) and needy (masakin), ensuring that Muslim donors can fulfill their religious obligations through <cite id=\"9\">verified humanitarian projects</cite>.",
